{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-detail-page-js","path":"/your-performance-at-work","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Buckinghamshire HR service desk","basePath":"https://bucks-temp-name.com","gaConfig":{"id":"UA-129132977-3"}}},"contentfulPage":{"title":"Your performance at work (C4P)","metaTitle":"Your performance at work (C4P)","metaDescription":"Find out why you and your manager should talk to each other regularly to help you perform well, how to set goals with your manager, and what your six monthly performance reviews involve","parentPage":null,"intro":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The more you and your manager communicate, the easier it is for your manager to support you. It’s a good idea to have frequent chats about your short term goals, and then review these every three months. You’ll also have a more formal review twice a year to check on how you’re doing. </p>"}},"body":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Our performance management process is called Coaching for Performance, and it’s all about open and clear communication between managers and the people they manage. Everyone should feel able to ask questions and get guidance whenever they need to. </p>\n<p>It’s best to have a mix of informal chats and more formal and structured meetings several times a year.  </p>\n<p>We have produced a short video to help explain Coaching for Performance:</p>\n<iframe style=\"width:100%; height:40vw;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/YXQpVq8Aibo\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n    "}},"hero":{"headline":"Performance hero","subHeading":null,"image":[{"title":"Performance Hero Large 2","description":"","file":{"details":{"size":476815,"image":{"width":1440,"height":450}},"fileName":"large01.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/5MFXgo2xw6nJbhLThXLUHy/27809228728daa0c3eec3b63fefbb20f/large01.jpg"}},{"title":"Performance Hero Medium 2","description":"","file":{"details":{"size":256790,"image":{"width":800,"height":375}},"fileName":"medium01.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/1GtshQ9DhtusJqBaUwDFdt/77b517ead6d44ae888723a6a00e50d7f/medium01.jpg"}},{"title":"Performance Hero Small 2","description":"","file":{"details":{"size":128400,"image":{"width":440,"height":300}},"fileName":"small01.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/lj5FPjI2HKAwzMqpiiOR8/5f391f5613303ffe2b0ecb4b45677112/small01.jpg"}}]},"collapsibleLinks":[{"title":"Informal chats","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Talking regularly with your manager is a good way of keeping in touch about the work you’re doing. It’s also a chance to talk through what’s going well and not so well and get support. </p>\n<p>If you have a query or a problem, ask your manager for a chat there and then (face to face or by phone, etc). It’s much better to talk about it immediately than wait for a scheduled meeting.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":" Reviewing and setting goals","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Every three months, it’s a good idea for you and your manager to have a more formal meeting. This will help you set your direction and review how you’re performing. </p>"}},"open":null,"link":{"id":"39198378-94af-5580-baa0-448145109df1","title":"Reviewing and setting goals ","slug":"reviewing-and-setting-goals"},"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Performance reviews ","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>You must have two formal performance reviews each year in March and September. Your manager then rates how you’ve performed, based on how well you’ve met your goals, how well your behaviour matches our values ‘PACT’, and how well you’ve carried out your role.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":{"id":"930fdc5f-ac67-506f-b847-6229569bf26a","title":"Your performance review","slug":"your-performance-review"},"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Mandatory training ","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>There are six key online training modules that all of us need to go on. Think of them as the basic ground rules of how we work safely together. </p>"}},"open":null,"link":{"id":"7f6300a2-de75-5c16-ba3c-27f436de1f60","title":"Mandatory training","slug":"mandatory-training"},"mediaLink":null}],"mediaLink":[{"id":"ea862f56-8068-5cff-a7ea-53186af855c3","type":"doc","title":"BC Coaching for Performance Toolkit","mediaLink":null,"description":null,"mediaFile":{"file":{"fileName":"updated C4P toolkit 30 Dec 2020.pdf","url":"//assets.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/rz0uFxHAxGQ0eRm4dXavj/c328ee8c02115f4da074138e700f50ef/updated_C4P_toolkit_30_Dec_2020.pdf"}}}]}},"pageContext":{"id":"7b0e05d9-a0bb-55c8-a0fc-b1b64b9ab04b","map":{"510eff4f-2b1f-5b23-a329-8c19f43773ed":"holidays-and-time-off/annual-leave","d95dbc68-e229-5dd8-8a67-de32e90c3a11":"training-and-development/step-up-to-social-work","930fdc5f-ac67-506f-b847-6229569bf26a":"your-performance-at-work/your-performance-review","bead0121-d209-5eaa-907c-d64ca7a314a5":"training-and-development/upskilling-apprenticeships","458dc126-bc87-5700-af41-d7b61aff4a95":"training-and-development/new-talent-apprenticeships","a7172d78-188e-59fb-81f1-d49b18ca1979":"training-and-development/on-demand-management-apprenticeship-programmes","0e7a6481-b2c7-574e-80a0-34aa1f8cd8d3":"how-we-recruit-people/getting-approval-to-recruit","66fa88ab-b900-555e-8deb-1e53b41d3814":"how-we-recruit-people/recruiting-agency-workers","6acbf4fa-7b21-51d3-a267-f060cf1d9dbf":"values-at-work/trustworthy","ba96fa6d-873b-5756-91f0-3a4b38158e5f":"values-at-work/collaborative","fefbbb2a-1c8e-5761-acf3-e53d689d6d83":"values-at-work/ambitious","6ba63441-c932-5f9c-8eed-8fb0f307ab7d":"values-at-work/proud","9dcc0517-92be-542d-9822-655116289c9d":"how-we-recruit-people/interviews-and-assessments","c46f43ce-d